# Reproductive System

> The reproductive system consists of **organs, ducts, and accessory glands** responsible for producing, storing, and transporting gametes, and — in females — supporting fertilisation, gestation, and parturition. It is closely related to the urinary system (→ [[Urinary System]]) and is innervated by the autonomic nervous system.

## 🔗 Key Connections
- [[00 - AnatomyLink Home]]
- Arterial supply: Internal iliac artery → branches to pelvic viscera
- Venous drainage: Gonadal veins → IVC (right) / left renal vein (left)
- Lymphatics: Para-aortic nodes (gonads), internal iliac nodes (uterus, prostate)
- Innervation: [[Sacral Plexus]], hypogastric plexus (sympathetic), pelvic splanchnic nerves (parasympathetic)
- Skeletal relations: [[Coccyx]], [[Lumbar Vertebrae]], pelvic bones ([[Ischial Tuberosity]], [[Anterior Superior Iliac Spine]])
- Hormonal control: Hypothalamic–pituitary–gonadal (HPG) axis → GnRH → LH / FSH

